A worker came to fix the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but I was actually editing "Addicted".
If only this damn file could open properly. (OneDrive is a complete piece of junk.)
The hacker's voice said, I'm in.
He started drilling, the noise was super loud. Great.
I cranked up the air purifier to the maximum setting, and it felt a bit too intense, but I had indeed caught a whiff of wood shavings, so doing so wasn't entirely unreasonable, to say nothing of his opposition to wearing a mask. Plus, I really did need to protect myself, didn't I?
I really wish I could go back to sleep, but I won't be able to sleep until he leaves.
The good news is that Chapter Four is finally edited!
Chapter Five is really lengthy, making me super anxious. Yay! I'm really into this.
Chapter Five is really lengthy, making me super anxious. Yay! I'm really into this. I'm currently searching and replacing, ... , by the way, this chapter has 54 of them.
But I still want to hold onto this point. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally agitated.
The floor repairman is using a vacuum to clean, hopefully that means he's almost done.
The worker is apparently cutting something outside, I sneak a peek at my progress. There's still a lot of work to do :(
Chapter Five still has seven pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in great shape, mainly just some minor adjustments to the formatting and a few tweaks to make it more active and concise. I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, but that guy is still working away in my kitchen.
He's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The worker fixing the kitchen floor is gone!
The worker told me he quoted the price for the entire floor repair, but the landlord is too frugal and only agreed to pay for the repair of the rotten spot right by the entrance. That's a relief.
I'm sipping tea in the garden while the air purifier in the kitchen is working hard to clean the air in the room!
